              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Recovery typically takes one full update cycle — three to nine months for core updates, weeks to months for spam updates. You cannot request review; the site is re-evaluated when the algorithm re-runs.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">Algorithmic penalty vs manual action — what is the difference?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>A manual action is applied by a human reviewer at Google and appears in Search Console with a specific reason. An algorithmic penalty is applied automatically by ranking systems, is not reported anywhere, and clears only when the algorithm re-evaluates the site.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
